<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="449" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,591]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,533,556]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">Remarks.</emphasis>
Having examined the 
<typeStatus box="[581,674,533,556]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis box="[725,893,532,556]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shang &amp; Zhang. A" authorityYear="2006" box="[725,889,532,556]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Favintiga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilipenis">F. gracilipenis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
we provide additional morphological data and illustrations. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Lu &amp; Zhang, 2018" authorityName="Lu &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2018" box="[560,764,567,591]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Favintiga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paragracilipenis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[560,764,567,591]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">F. paragracilipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[771,853,568,591]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
but the latter has a shorter connective process.
</paragraph>
